  "commentary": "With SPX at 6608 trading just above the GEX flip at 6606 and surrounded by massive positive gamma walls, dealers are in heavy sell-the-rally mode as they hedge their long gamma positions. The 6605 strike holds the largest positive GEX at 12.8B, creating significant resistance, while the wall_break and gex_surge events suggest we just punched through a key level with dealers now scrambling to rehedge. Expect strong mean reversion pressure back toward the 6605-6606 pivot zone, with the 6610 (+9.3B GEX) acting as the next major resistance wall if the current level fails to hold.\n\nBottom line: expect a pullback toward 6605 as dealers sell into this move above their key hedging level.",
